The paper deals with optimization problems on machines, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The use of convex programming and LP-rounding algorithms suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) categories. The focus on approximation algorithms and optimization suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Finally, the use of numerical methods and optimization techniques suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category.
